BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Together\, They Made the Modern American Presidency
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T140000
UID:43db8b0dbe1eb80c701e945e114c3e44@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Presentation\, Teens\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nAdult program\, old
 er teens are welcome. Please register for each session.Dr. Robert Frick\, 
 local historian\, author\, and retired Lampeter Strasburg School District 
 Superintendent\, has developed a number of lecture series to inform and en
 tertain you with objective\, non-partisan content.  This series focuses on
  the modern American Presidency.The framers of the U.S. Constitution were 
 wary of the Executive Branch\, the most likely source of tyranny in the go
 vernment. Having escaped the authority of a king\, they wanted no more of 
 it or an executive who would dominate the new government\; thus\, the care
 ful wording of Article II. As leaders\, Presidents need to communicate wit
 h the public\, build a team\, be assertive\, create overarching goals\, pr
 ocess information\, and manage their emotions. These qualities come in var
 ying degrees and sundry types with each new President. Historians believe 
 it takes 20 years to properly evaluate a presidency\, therefore this serie
 s culminates with the 43rd president.February 27 –  FDR\, TrumanMarch 6 
 – Eisenhower\, KennedyMarch 13 –  Johnson\, NixonMarch 20 –  Ford\, 
 CarterMarch 27 – Reagan\, GHW BushApril 3 - Library closed April 10 – 
 Clinton\, GW Bush
LOCATION:Quarryville\, QVL C.X. Carlson Cultural Room
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/together-they-made-moder
 n-american-presidency-146576
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:STEM Windcars
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T144500
UID:45d05e678d5f282c4325fc6abd08a907@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:STEM\, Children\n\nWhat's a "Wind Car"? Well\, it's a kind of 
 car that only you can create that is powered by wind - or\, in this case\,
  a box fan. With a little science\, technology\, engineering\, and math - 
 we'll see what we can put together and how far it will go. Join us on Frid
 ay\, April 10th as we create\, test\, and evaluate our very own Wind Cars.
   Registration opens for Manheim Township and East Lampeter residents on W
 ednesday\, April 25th at 9:00 AM and on Wednesday\, April 1st at 9:00 AM f
 or all other residents.  Library Program Policies No Show – Patrons fa
 iling to cancel their registration for more than 2 library programs in a m
 onth will be restricted from registering for future programs for a period 
 of one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hours p
 rior to the start of the program to allow those on the waiting list to be 
 notified of their change in registration status. Late Arrivals – Pleas
 e arrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for par
 king and other circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the desig
 nated time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wai
 t list who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be all
 owed into the program. However\, registrants will not be permitted to 
 enter the program 5 minutes past the start time. Drop Off Program – Th
 is program is intended for children over the age of 6 years who can partic
 ipate independently. Adult(s) must be present to check in child with youth
  services staff prior to program. Adults will not be allowed in the event 
 space.  *For children ages 6–7\, this is a drop-off program\; howeve
 r\, a parent or caregiver must remain nearby and wait outside the progra
 m room for the duration of the program. Photography The Manheim Township
  Public Library Code of Conduct Policy prohibits photographing or video re
 cording individuals (including children) without their consent (or in the 
 case of a child\, the consent of a parent or guardian).
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Morgan Center A
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/stem-windcars-166379
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
