 nse\, great conversation\, and maybe a few red herrings along the way.Regi
 stration is encouragedJanuary 12: The Puzzle Box by Danielle TrussoniFebru
 ary 9: The New Girl by Daniel SilvaMarch 9: The Stolen Queen by Fiona Davi
 sApril 13: Crime Scene by Jonathan & Jesse KellermanMay 11: Quiet Libraria
 n by Allen EskensJune 8: Footprints of God by Greg IilesJuly 13: The 7½ D
 eaths of Evelyn Hardcastle by Stuart TurtonAugust 10: Death & Judgement by
  Donna LeonSeptember 14: How to Solve Your Own Murder by Kristin PerrinOct
 ober 12: The Secret of Secrets by Dan BrownNovember 9: All the Colors of t
 he Dark by Christ WhitakerDecember 14: The Twelve Books of Christmas by Ka
 te Carlisle
