DESCRIPTION:Community\, Gaming\, Adults\n\nJoin local GM Matt as he runs a
  variety of Tabletop Role Playing Games that rotate each month. No experie
 nce in any system is required and anyone interested in dipping their toes 
 into the TTRPG world are welcomed and encouraged to join in on the fun!Thi
 s month’s game is Dungeons and Dragons 5e. Welcome delicious adventurers
  to the world of Calorum!! A land where the question “What would happen 
 if Candyland and Game of Thrones had a baby?”.Calorum is a fantasy setti
 ng like many others. Noble clans with hereditary titles wage war for petty
  reasons\, marry off their family members to secure power and try to maint
 ain their hold on the population they have legally bound to service. There
  is\, however\, a difference: everything is made out of food. Peasants mad
 e of pink gelatin gather licorice for their liege lord\, nobles with skin 
 of parmesan build forts out of cheesestone and bread blacksmiths carve fet
 tucine into weapons of war. Registration is required. This group is for ad
 ults but check our calendar for other ages.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Morgan Center C
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/tabletop-rpgs-adults-165
