DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260416T143000
UID:dd3e8aa297917bc6426d8947e2662a13@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Technology Class\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nWe will equip you with 
 some skills and strategies needed to navigate today’s digital landscape\
 , helping you recognize the subtle artifacts and patterns indicative of AI
 -generated media. Through hands-on analysis of synthetic images\, deepfake
  videos\, and algorithmically produced news\, you will be able to learn te
 chniques necessary to separate machine-made fiction from human reality. Th
 is class is supported by a grant from the OpenAI Foundation. Ages 18+.
LOCATION:Ephrata\, EPH Conference Room
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/spotting-fake-161753
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
