BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:America250 in Manheim
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260418T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260418T203000
UID:6c9f892bc4dd4f9aa15575b86ae44ae3@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Arts & Crafts\, Community\, Discussion\, Fundraiser\, Music\, 
 Presentation\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nTo Purchase your Tickets\, Use This Evi
 te Link: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/1982453951134?aff=oddtdtcreatorGet r
 eady to dive into the flavors of American history with A Taste of History-
 America250 in Manheim Fundraiser - a delicious journey awaitsOn Saturday\,
  April 18th\, the Manheim Historical Society and Manheim Community Library
  invite you to join them as we take a look back in time and toast five Ame
 rican patriots who have significant connections to Manheim. With each wine
  tasting experience offered by Glasshouse Wineworks of Manheim\, a unique 
 wine is made for each patriot\, and each person's story is told. Desserts 
 and hors d'oeuvres associated with the era will also be served. Visitors m
 ay sit and catch up with friends\, make new acquaintances\, and savor a ca
 sh bar of wine and beer as they walk from wine station to wine station. We
  appreciate all proceeds\, which will help the Manheim Community Library a
 nd Manheim Historical Society maintain our local history while promoting r
 eading and lifelong learning.What's included for adults over 21:General Ad
 mission pay $75 for a standard ticket that includes desserts\, hors d'oeuv
 res\, and wine tastings. Cash bar of wine and beer available.VIP tickets a
 re $95 and include everything described above\, as well as a personalized 
 wine glass and one glass of your favorite wine.Tickets must be pre-purchas
 ed online or by mailing checks made payable to Manheim Historical Society 
 to Box 396\, Manheim\, PA 17545. Kindly specify the type and quantity of t
 ickets. Tickets must be purchased in advance\, by April 10th.The Kreider F
 arms Cultural Center will open its doors for check-in at 5:45 p.m. At 6:15
  p.m.\, wine- tasting tables will open. Bottles of wine will be available 
 for purchase at the event but will be held until end of event.
LOCATION:Manheim Community\, MAN Kreider Cultural Center
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/america250-manheim-16177
 5
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
