 y dogs will be at the library twice a month for students and emerging read
 ers to get more comfortable reading out loud in a judgement-free environme
 nt. The 1st Saturday of each month will always be 2 of either Brodie\, Bro
 oklyn\, or Jessie all from the same owner (medium sized dogs that look lik
 e the image on the posters). The 3rd Saturday of the month will have k-pet
 s volunteers who register on their own when available. We may get a broad 
 range of dog breeds and personalities. Feel free to attend both or opt for
  just one.Registration for this program offers you the chance to make sure
  you get a time slot. After all registered patrons arrive\, walk-ins will 
 be allowed on the list. Each child will get a 10-minute time slot to start
 . If you would like a second slot\, you can get on the waitlist by telling
  Miss Esther. If there are spots left\, it will be first come first serve.
 If you can't make it after registering\, please contact Miss Esther at ema
 rtin@manheimlibrary.org or call (717)665-6700 Ext. 4200 for the circulatio
 n desk so we can take you off the list and allow everyone a chance.When yo
 u arrive\, you will need a book to read. You have the library at your disp
 osal or you can bring your own. You can start halfway if you want. Read wh
 atever you like!
