 t be 18 months-younger 3 years old with an adult\, adult involvement is re
 quired)Adults attending with their child(ren) do NOT need to register. Ple
 ase add any additional registrants to your registration if more than one c
 hild that will be participating in the program.Registration will open at 9
 :00AM on Wednesday\, April 22nd for Manheim Township and East Lampeter res
 idents and on Friday\, April 24th for residents of other municipalities.St
 orytime PoliciesNo Show – Patrons failing to cancel their registration f
 or more than 2 library programs in a month will be restricted from registe
 ring for future programs for a period of one month’s time. Please cancel
  your registrations at least 2 hours prior to the start of the program to 
 allow for those on the waiting list to be notified of their change in regi
 stration status.Late Arrivals – Please arrive 10 minutes prior to the st
 art of the program to allow for parking and other circumstances. The progr
 am will begin promptly at the designated time. At this time\, your spot wi
 ll be forfeited to those on the wait list who will be granted entry. If sp
 ots remain\, registrants may be allowed into the program. However\, regist
 rants will not be permitted to enter the program 5 minutes past the start 
 time.Accompanying Adults – This program is for adults and children to en
 joy together. Please plan to attend and be engaged with your child. Drop o
 ffs will not be permitted.Cancellations- Please check your email prior to 
