BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Dungeons and Dragons Adventure Club for Kids (Ages 9-12 only)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260506T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260506T183000
UID:3e2b40c5eb692e676577dbd12ba9d23e@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Gaming\, Children\, Tweens\n\nCalling all young adventurers ag
 es 9 to 12! Join us for an exciting journey into the world of Dungeons & D
 ragons\, where your imagination sets the course. Together\, we’ll learn 
 how to create unique characters\, navigate magical lands\, and solve thril
 ling quests. No prior experience is needed—new and experienced players a
 like are welcome!In each session\, you'll explore stories full of mystery\
 , monsters\, and more all while working as a team to overcome challenges a
 nd puzzles. Whether you're a brave warrior\, a clever wizard\, or a sneaky
  rogue\, there’s always an adventure waiting. Are you ready to roll the 
 dice and discover where the story leads?Spaces are limited\, so sign up to
 day to secure your spot in our grand adventure! All materials will be prov
 ided.Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, April 22nd for Manhei
 m Township and East Lampeter residents and on Wednesday\, April 29th for r
 esidents of other municipalities.LIBRARY PROGRAM POLICIES:Drop Off Program
  – This program is intended for children over the age of 9 years who can
  participate independently. Adult(s) must be present to check in child wit
 h youth services staff prior to program. Adults will not be allowed in the
  event space. Designated Ages – Please adhere to the age restrictions de
 signated on your registration. Only children in that age range will be adm
 itted.Registration Requirements –  To help us manage our space\, please 
 register every person who will be attending\, including siblings.No Show 
 – Patrons failing to cancel their registration for more than 2 library p
 rograms in a month will be restricted from registering for future programs
  for a period of one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at l
 east 2 hours prior to the start of the program to allow for those on the w
 aiting list to be notified of their change in registration status.Late Arr
 ivals – Please arrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to al
 low for parking and other circumstances. The program will begin promptly a
 t the designated time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those
  on the wait list who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants
  may be allowed into the program. However\, registrants will not be permit
 ted to enter the program 5 minutes past the start time.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Morgan Center B
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/dungeons-and-dragons-adv
 enture-club-kids-ages-9-12-only-154351
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
