SUMMARY:Understanding Human Trafficking in Our Community
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260519T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260519T190000
UID:c2dd57c1d673c16af200d645de4504c9@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, Adults\n\nPAATH15 Crossroads\, a project of the YW
 CA Greater Harrisburg\, is a regional network of expertly trained service 
 providers working to combat labor and sex trafficking across Central Penns
 ylvania. In this engaging and informative session\, Barb Bingham\, Communi
 ty Engagement and Training Specialist\, will share insight into how human 
 trafficking affects our communities and what we can do to address it. The 
 presentation is designed to raise awareness\, increase identification\, an
 d empower attendees to recognize and respond to trafficking situations saf
 ely and effectively. Whether you're a concerned citizen\, community leader
  or frontline professional\, this session will provide practical tools and
  a deeper understanding of this critical issue. Learn the signs. Understan
 d the impact. Be part of the solution. Ages 18+.
LOCATION:Ephrata\, EPH 1/2 Multipurpose Room Projector Side
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/ywca-program-158698
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
