BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Kids' Garden Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260527T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260527T174500
UID:df4301441a50d5d7d6b331777acfc02d@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Children\n\nSpring has sprung and it's time for so
 me garden fun!  Join us on our patio for our exciting garden time!  (Rain 
 or shine - if it's raining\, we'll be meeting indoors and limit our outsid
 e time.)  We'll read some stories\, do some crafts\, and of course\, get o
 ur hands in that soil and plant some seeds!  ***This week we'll take one f
 inal look at seeds with my favorite book "The Bad Seed".  We'll create our
  very own "Bad Seed" and of course\, we'll get our hands dirty in our pots
  tending to our plants.***We'll supply the seeds\, the tools\, and the pla
 nters - you supply your own gloves.  Plan on getting a little dirty.  This
  program is for children ages 6 - 9 years old.  Registration will open at 
 9:00AM on Wednesday\, May 13th for Manheim Township and East Lampeter resi
 dents and on Wednesday\, May 20th for residents of other municipalities.Li
 brary Program Policies No Show – Patrons failing to cancel their regis
 tration for more than 2 library programs in a month will be restricted fro
 m registering for future programs for a period of one month’s time. Plea
 se cancel your registrations at least 2 hours prior to the start of the pr
 ogram to allow those on the waiting list to be notified of their change in
  registration status. Late Arrivals – Please arrive 10 minutes prior
  to the start of the program to allow for parking and other circumstance
 s. The program will begin promptly at the designated time. At this time\, 
 your spot will be forfeited to those on the wait list who will be granted 
 entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be allowed into the program. Howe
 ver\, registrants will not be permitted to enter the program 5 minutes
  past the start time. Drop Off Program – This program is intended for 
 children over the age of 6 years who can participate independently. Adult(
 s) must be present to check in child with youth services staff prior to pr
 ogram. Adults will not be allowed in the event space.  *For children age
 s 6–7\, this is a drop-off program\; however\, a parent or caregiver
  must remain nearby and wait outside the program room for the duration
  of the program. Photography The Manheim Township Public Library Code of C
 onduct Policy prohibits photographing or video recording individuals (incl
 uding children) without their consent (or in the case of a child\, the con
 sent of a parent or guardian).
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Patio
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/kids-garden-club-170442
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
