UID:93acb5d10b76a2b2e6da5ac214c462ea@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, Health & Wellness\, Presentation\, Adults\, Senior
 s\n\nDid you know that in the 1800s\, terrariums were "survival pods" used
  to transport tea plants across the ocean? Join us to discover how these g
 lass enclosures changed the world-- and how they can bring a self-sustaini
 ng slice of nature into your home today!What You’ll Learn:The Foundation
 : Essential prep steps to take before you start building.The Kit: A guide 
 to the specific supplies needed for a thriving ecosystem.The Build: Master
  the art of layering and assembly.The Longevity: Pro-tips for long-term ca
 re and quick fixes for common plant issues.Whether you have a green thumb 
 or a history of unintentional plant homicide\, this session will give you 
 the skills to maintain a miniature world that practically takes care of it
 self 🌿Presented by the Penn State Extension Master Gardeners
